f Queen Victoria, 1837-1861,\"] ''The Dublin Review,'' Vol. CXLII, January/April 1908.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/dublinreview143londuoft#page/60/mode/2up \"Christian Science,\"] ''The Dublin Review,'' Vol. CXLIII, No. 286, October 1908.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/dublinreview145londuoft#page/406/mode/2up \"Spiritualism,\"] ''The Dublin Review,'' Vol. CXLV, No. 290-291, July/October, 1909.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/dublinreview146londuoft#page/382/mode/2up \"A Catholic Colony,\"] ''The Dublin Review,'' Vol. CXLVI, January/April, 1910.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/atlantic106bostuoft#page/166/mode/2up \"Catholicism and the Future,\"] ''The Atlantic Monthly'', Vol. CVI, 1910.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/dublinreview150londuoft#page/42/mode/2up \"Phantasms of the Dead,\"] ''The Dublin Review,'' Vol. CL, No. 300-301, January/April, 1912.\n* [http://www.unz.org/Pub/NorthAmericanRev-1912sep-00353 \"Cosmopolitanism and Catholicism,\"] ''The North American Review,'' September 1912.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/dublinreview155londuoft#page/124/mode/2up \"Cardinal Gasquet,\"] ''The Dublin Review,'' Vol. CLV, July/October, 1914.\n\n'''Other'''\n* [https://archive.org/stream/holyblissfulmart00bensuoft#page/n5/mode/2up ''The Holy Blissful Martyr Saint Thomas of Canterbury,''] Benziger Brothers, 1910.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/lifeofsaintteres00bensrich#page/n9/mode/2up ''The Life of Saint Teresa,''] Herbert & Daniel, 1912.\n* [https://archive.org/stream/poemsbensonrober00bens#page/n9/mode/2up ''Poems,''] Burns & Oates, 1915.\n* ''Maxims from the Writings of Mgr. Benson, By the compiler of \"Thoughts from Augustine Birrell,\"'' R. & T. Washbourne Ltd., 1915.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Conservatism|Christianity|Catholicism}}\n* [[Gerard Manley Hopkins]]\n* [[John Henry Newman]]\n* [[G.K. Chesterton]]\n* [[List of dystopian literature]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==References==\n* Beesley, Thomas Quinn (1916). [https://archive.org/stream/catholiceducatio12cathuoft#page/122/mode/2up \"The Poetry of Robert Hugh Benson,\"] ''The Catholic Educational Review,'' Vol. XII, pp.&nbsp;122\u2013134.\n* Benson, Arthur C. (1915). [https://archive.org/stream/cu31924029429036#page/n9/mode/2up ''Hugh: Memoir of a Brother.''] London: Smith, Elder & Co.\n* Bleiler, Everett (1948). ''The Checklist of Fantastic Literature.'' Chicago: Shasta Publishers.\n* Bour'his, Jean Morris le (1980). ''Robert Hugh Benson, Homme de Foi et Artiste.'' Atelier Reproduction de Th\u00e8ses, Universit\u00e9 de Lille III.\n* Braybrooke, Patrick (1931). \"Robert Hugh Benson; Novelist and Philosopher.\" In: ''Some Catholic Novelists.'' London: Burns, Oates & Washbourne.\n* Brown, Stephen J.M. & Thomas McDermott (1945). [http://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=mdp.39076006824432;view=1up;seq=7 ''A Survey of Catholic Literature.''] Milwaukee: The Bruce Publishing Company.\n* [[Helena Concannon|Concannon, Helena]] (1914). [https://archive.org/stream/catholicworld99pauluoft#page/486/mode/2up \"Robert Hugh Benson, Novelist,\"] [https://archive.org/stream/catholicworld99pauluoft#page/634/mode/2up Part II,] ''The Catholic World,'' Vol. XCIX, pp.&nbsp;487\u2013498, 635\u2013645.\n* Gorce, Agn\u00e8s de La (1928). ''Robert Hugh Benson: Pr\u00eatre et Romancier, 1871-1914.'' Paris: Plon.\n* Grayson, Janet (1998). ''Robert Hugh Benson: Life and Works.'' Lanham, Md.: University Press of America.\n* Watt, Reginald J.J. (1918). [https://archive.org/stream/roberthughbenson00watt#page/n7/mode/2up ''Robert Hugh Benson: Captain in God's Army.''] London: Burns & Oates Ldt.\n* [[Blanche Warre-Cornish|Warre Cornish, Blanche]] (1914). [https://archive.org/stream/memorialsofrober00warriala#page/n9/mode/2up ''Memorials of Robert Hugh Benson.''] New York: P.J. Kenedy & Sons.\n* McMahon, Joseph H. (1915). [https://archive.org/stream/recordsofamerica26ameruoft#page/54/mode/2up \"The Late Monsignor Robert Hugh Benson,\"] ''Records of the American Catholic Historical Society of Philadelphi